---
title: Sweet 'N' Savory Chicken Fried Rice with Pineapple, Carrots, and Peas
description: If you’re looking for a recipe that packs in a basket-load of wholesome produce and proteins without tasting or feeling too much like health food, fried rice has got you covered. Our fully loaded version has peas, pineapple, carrots, onion, cashews, eggs, and chicken—all tucked into a nice helping of Uncle Ben's® Ready Rice® Jasmine. Thankfully, all that goodness can be prepared in a single pan and is ready in thirty minutes flat.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/sweet-n-savory-chicken-fried-rice-14d7eb00.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/sweet-n-savory-chicken-fried-rice-19c40579.pdf
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/sweet-n-savory-chicken-fried-rice-598cc78c51d3f1555d3cb762
time required: 30 minutes
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 630 kcal
  fat: 20 g
  saturated fat: 3 g
  carbohydrates: 83 g
  sugar: 23 g
  protein: 33 g
  fiber: 6 g
  sodium: 840 mg
servings: 2
---

Wash and dry all produce. Drain @pineapple{16%ounce}. Halve @lime{1}; cut one half
into wedges. Halve, peel, and dice @red onion{1}. Cut @chicken breasts{12%ounce}
into ½-inch cubes.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tablespoon} in a large pan over medium-high
heat. Add chicken and @hoisin sauce{1.25%ounce} and cook, tossing, until
browned and cooked through, ~{4-5%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}. Remove from pan and set aside. Wipe or rinse out any charred bits
in pan.

Add onion and a large drizzle of oil to same pan over medium-high heat. Cook
until softened, about ~{3%minutes}. Add pineapple and @shredded carrots{4%ounce}
and toss until pineapple is browned and carrots are tender, ~{4-5%minutes}. Season
with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add @Uncle Ben's Ready Rice Jasmine{17.6%ounce} to pan along with chicken and
@peas{4%ounce}. Toss to thoroughly combine, breaking up rice until there are no
more clumps. Stir until rice is warmed through and tender, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Push contents of pan to the sides, making a 3-inch well in the center (you should
see the bottom of the pan). Crack @eggs{2} into well and beat vigorously to
scramble, then toss into the other ingredients.

Remove pan from heat. Stir in @soy sauce{4%tablespoon}, @sesame oil{1%tablespoon},
and a squeeze of lime. Divide everything between bowls. Tear @cilantro{1/2%ounce}
leaves from stems and scatter over top, then sprinkle with @cashews{2%ounce}.
Drizzle @sriracha{2%teaspoon} over the adults' bowls. Serve with lime wedges on
the side for squeezing over.

> This fully loaded fried rice has peas, pineapple, carrots, onion, cashews, eggs,
> and chicken—all tucked into a nice helping of Uncle Ben's Ready Rice Jasmine.
> All that goodness can be prepared in a single pan and is ready in thirty minutes
> flat.